# Trivy CVE ignore / triage ledger
#
# This operator is a thin layer on top of the upstream
# `quay.io/operator-framework/helm-operator` base image (see operator/Dockerfile):
# we only COPY Helm charts and watches.yaml on top of it. We do not build any
# Go binaries ourselves, so every CVE below lives in the base image (its UBI RPMs
# or the bundled `helm-operator` binary) and can only be fixed by upstream
# shipping a rebuilt base image.
#
# HOW TO FIX A FINDING (in priority order):
#   1. Preferred: bump the base image digest in operator/Dockerfile to a newer
#      operator-framework/helm-operator release that ships the fix. Org-level
#      Renovate opens these digest-bump PRs automatically; this is the real fix.
#   2. If no fixed base image exists yet, record the CVE here with a short note
#      and a date so CI stays green while the finding is tracked. Re-check and
#      prune entries whenever the base image is bumped.
#
# Review the entries below each time operator/Dockerfile's base image changes and
# delete any that the new base image resolves.

# --- Accepted: 2026-06-14 ---
# All HIGH severity, all upstream-only. The newest helm-operator release (v1.42.2)
# and its `latest` rebuild both still carry these, so there is no fixed base image
# to bump to yet. Tracked here until operator-framework ships a patched release.

